Fitting The Random Forest Regressor Model with the list of parameters in the RandomizedSearchCV Algorithm and getting the r2 Score between the predicted value and dependent test dataset



















In [47]:



     


n_estimators = [int(x) for x in np.linspace(start = 80, stop = 1500, num = 10)]
max_features = ['auto', 'sqrt']
max_depth = [int(x) for x in np.linspace(6, 45, num = 5)]
min_samples_split = [2, 5, 10, 15, 100]
min_samples_leaf = [1, 2, 5, 10]

rand_grid={'n_estimators': n_estimators,
               'max_features': max_features,
               'max_depth': max_depth,
               'min_samples_split': min_samples_split,
               'min_samples_leaf': min_samples_leaf}
rf=RandomForestRegressor()

rCV=RandomizedSearchCV(estimator=rf,param_distributions=rand_grid,scoring='neg_mean_squared_error',
                       n_iter=10,cv=3,random_state=42, n_jobs = 1)

rCV.fit(x_train,y_train)
rf_pred=rCV.predict(x_test)
r2_score(y_test,rf_pred)



     






















    
    
Out[47]:








0.8115715357392459
